This paper deals with multi-agent systems and probabilistic reasoning, which are topics that are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also presents a novel syntax and semantics for the system, which involves logical reasoning (cs.LO) and modal logic (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper discusses applications to reasoning about game playing agents, which falls under the category of computational game theory (cs.PL).
